This paper is about deep learning techniques for image super-resolution, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of recurrent networks, dense connections, and residual learning, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves image processing and manipulation, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the use of iterative up- and down-sampling layers suggests the use of neural networks with feedback mechanisms, which could fall under neural networks (cs.NE).
